I'll continue with the detailed elaboration of the remaining phases.

---

#### Phase 4: Frontend Rendering and Interaction

This phase transforms the raw timeline data into an engaging, interactive user experience. The frontend must faithfully represent the conversation while adding value through intelligent presentation and navigation.

**Why This Architecture Matters:**
* **Component Reusability:** Building a modular component system means each timeline event type can be independently tested, styled, and evolved without affecting others.
* **Performance:** For large conversations with hundreds of events, proper virtualization and lazy-loading patterns prevent UI lag.
* **Semantic Understanding:** The UI can now make intelligent decisions. For example, it can visually distinguish between an agent's internal reasoning and its final output, or show which code changes were automatic vs. user-initiated.

**Implementation Instructions:**

1. **Create the Timeline Component Architecture (`app/src/components/conversation/`):**

   I will create a component hierarchy that mirrors the data structure:

   ```
   app/src/components/conversation/
   ├── Timeline.tsx                    (Main container, handles virtualization)
   ├── TimelineEvent.tsx               (Event router component)
   ├── events/
   │   ├── UserPromptEvent.tsx
   │   ├── AssistantTurnEvent.tsx
   │   ├── ToolResultEvent.tsx
   │   └── ParsingErrorEvent.tsx
   ├── blocks/
   │   ├── TextBlock.tsx
   │   ├── ToolCallBlock.tsx
   │   └── ThoughtBlock.tsx
   └── ui/
       ├── CodeDiff.tsx
       ├── AgentBadge.tsx
       └── Timestamp.tsx
   ```

2. **Implement the Main Timeline Container (`Timeline.tsx`):**

   ```tsx
   import { Conversation } from '@howicc/schemas';
   import { TimelineEvent } from './TimelineEvent';
   import { Virtuoso } from 'react-virtuoso'; // For performance with large timelines

   interface TimelineProps {
     conversation: Conversation;
   }

   export function Timeline({ conversation }: TimelineProps) {
     return (
       <div className="conversation-timeline">
         {/* Header with metadata */}
         <div className="timeline-header">
           <h1>{conversation.title}</h1>
           <div className="metadata">
             <span className="project">{conversation.project}</span>
             <span className="branch">{conversation.gitBranch}</span>
             <span className="date">{new Date(conversation.createdAt).toLocaleDateString()}</span>
           </div>
         </div>

         {/* Virtualized timeline for performance */}
         <Virtuoso
           data={conversation.timeline}
           itemContent={(index, event) => (
             <TimelineEvent key={event.id} event={event} index={index} />
           )}
           className="timeline-events"
         />
       </div>
     );
   }
   ```

3. **Implement the Event Router (`TimelineEvent.tsx`):**

   This component acts as a discriminator, routing each event to its specialized renderer:

   ```tsx
   import { TimelineEvent as TimelineEventType } from '@howicc/schemas';
   import { UserPromptEvent } from './events/UserPromptEvent';
   import { AssistantTurnEvent } from './events/AssistantTurnEvent';
   import { ToolResultEvent } from './events/ToolResultEvent';
   import { ParsingErrorEvent } from './events/ParsingErrorEvent';

   interface Props {
     event: TimelineEventType;
     index: number;
   }

   export function TimelineEvent({ event, index }: Props) {
     switch (event.type) {
       case 'user_prompt':
         return <UserPromptEvent event={event} index={index} />;
       case 'assistant_turn':
         return <AssistantTurnEvent event={event} index={index} />;
       case 'tool_result':
         return <ToolResultEvent event={event} index={index} />;
       case 'parsing_error':
         return <ParsingErrorEvent event={event} index={index} />;
       default:
         // TypeScript exhaustiveness check
         const _exhaustive: never = event;
         return null;
     }
   }
   ```

4. **Implement AssistantTurnEvent Component (Most Complex):**

   This is where the rich data structure truly shines. We can render text blocks, tool calls with diffs, and agent thoughts all within a single assistant turn.

   ```tsx
   import { AssistantTurnEvent as AssistantTurnEventType } from '@howicc/schemas';
   import { TextBlock } from '../blocks/TextBlock';
   import { ToolCallBlock } from '../blocks/ToolCallBlock';
   import { ThoughtBlock } from '../blocks/ThoughtBlock';
   import { useState } from 'react';

   interface Props {
     event: AssistantTurnEventType;
     index: number;
   }

   export function AssistantTurnEvent({ event, index }: Props) {
     const [showThoughts, setShowThoughts] = useState(false);

     return (
       <div className="timeline-event assistant-turn" data-event-id={event.id}>
         {/* Header with model info and timestamp */}
         <div className="event-header">
           <span className="badge assistant">Assistant</span>
           <span className="model">{event.model}</span>
           <span className="timestamp">{new Date(event.timestamp).toLocaleTimeString()}</span>
         </div>

         {/* Content blocks */}
         <div className="event-content">
           {event.content.map((block, i) => {
             if (block.type === 'text_block') {
               return <TextBlock key={i} block={block} />;
             }
             if (block.type === 'tool_call_block') {
               return <ToolCallBlock key={i} block={block} />;
             }
             return null;
           })}
         </div>

         {/* Agent thoughts (collapsible section) */}
         {event.thoughts && event.thoughts.length > 0 && (
           <div className="thoughts-section">
             <button
               className="thoughts-toggle"
               onClick={() => setShowThoughts(!showThoughts)}
             >
               {showThoughts ? '▼' : '▶'} Agent Thoughts ({event.thoughts.length})
             </button>
             {showThoughts && (
               <div className="thoughts-list">
                 {event.thoughts.map((thought, i) => (
                   <ThoughtBlock key={i} thought={thought} />
                 ))}
               </div>
             )}
           </div>
         )}

         {/* Stop reason indicator (for debugging) */}
         {event.stopReason !== 'end_turn' && (
           <div className="stop-reason">{event.stopReason}</div>
         )}
       </div>
     );
   }
   ```

5. **Implement ToolCallBlock with Diff Viewer:**

   This is a critical component that displays file modifications inline. We'll use a diff library for proper syntax highlighting.

   ```tsx
   import { ToolCallBlock as ToolCallBlockType } from '@howicc/schemas';
   import { parseDiff, Diff, Hunk } from 'react-diff-view';
   import 'react-diff-view/style/index.css';
   import { useState } from 'react';

   interface Props {
     block: ToolCallBlockType;
   }

   export function ToolCallBlock({ block }: Props) {
     const [expanded, setExpanded] = useState(false);

     return (
       <div className="tool-call-block" data-tool-id={block.id}>
         <div className="tool-header" onClick={() => setExpanded(!expanded)}>
           <span className="tool-icon">🔧</span>
           <span className="tool-name">{block.toolName}</span>
           {block.filePatches && (
             <span className="file-count">{block.filePatches.length} file(s)</span>
           )}
           <span className="expand-icon">{expanded ? '▼' : '▶'}</span>
         </div>

         {expanded && (
           <div className="tool-details">
             {/* Show tool input (collapsed by default for brevity) */}
             <details className="tool-input">
               <summary>Input Parameters</summary>
               <pre>{JSON.stringify(block.input, null, 2)}</pre>
             </details>

             {/* Show file diffs if present */}
             {block.filePatches && block.filePatches.length > 0 && (
               <div className="file-patches">
                 {block.filePatches.map((patch, i) => {
                   const files = parseDiff(patch.diff);
                   return (
                     <div key={i} className="file-patch">
                       <div className="patch-header">
                         <span className="patch-type">{patch.type}</span>
                         <span className="file-path">{patch.filePath}</span>
                       </div>
                       {files.map((file, j) => (
                         <Diff key={j} viewType="unified" diffType={file.type} hunks={file.hunks}>
                           {(hunks) => hunks.map((hunk) => <Hunk key={hunk.content} hunk={hunk} />)}
                         </Diff>
                       ))}
                     </div>
                   );
                 })}
               </div>
             )}
           </div>
         )}
       </div>
     );
   }
   ```

6. **Update the Conversation Page (`app/src/pages/[slug].tsx`):**

